                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9873: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tunis</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heisler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-10T19:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 10, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 11—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. Reliably informed that three Italian destroyers have taken refuge at Sousse;
                    that Tunisia is furnishing the Italian forces in Libya with ammunition and
                    supplies and that Italian vessels are proceeding to Tripoli through Tunisian
                    territorial waters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heisler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
